      "Safety Stand-down conducted with EHS Advisor and crew personnel",
      "BSEE initiated investigation on July 10, 2020"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 9, 2020, a spill incident occurred onboard the Helix Q4000 semisubmersible vessel while working for Shell Offshore Inc at Mississippi Canyon 657. A total of 57 barrels of SF Base fluid spilled into the Gulf of Mexico due to the standpipe gate valve and bleed off valve being left in the open position. The incident was caused by human error during a riser displacement operation where personnel failed to physically verify valve closure and did not use the task-specific Job Safety Analysis.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Update previous Safety Alert addressing this situation or write new Safety Alert to issue to industry"
    ],
